DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Field Museum - Events\\nCost: Included with admissi
 on\\nAges: All ages\\nCategory: General\\n\\nCome meet Field Museum Collec
 tions staff Chris Philipp and Julia Kennedy as they discuss rarely-display
 ed masks from the A.B. Lewis collection\, new contemporary items\, and var
 ious media from the Field's Papua New Guinea collection. At nearly 35\,000
  items\, the Field Museum cares for the largest collection of material fro
 m the country of Papua New Guinea currently in the United States. This ses
 sion is the fourth and final in our series that celebrates Wan Bel: aColle
 ctive Global Exhibition \, commemorating the country of Papua New Guinea's
  50th Anniversary of Independence.\\n\\nMore info: https://www.fieldmuseum
 .org/our-events/meet-a-scientist/papua-new-guinea-collections-celebration-
 4
